<plot>God Bless is a twenty-minute short film based on a homeless man in Palo Alto, California. Shot on Super 16mm, the film centers on a community of homeless people living in a creek bed. The film explores social structure and humanity while still focusing in on a very narrow and propagandistic view. The narrative follows that of Joe Buckley as he attempts to take care of his slightly disabled friend and to make sense of the distant and somewhat oppressive world around him.</plot><url>http://localhost:8983/solr/movie.html?217879</url></doc>
